MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Wheel
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 91
  mythName: Wheel
  omens:
  - '1. With a gust of groaning wind, the next

    Season begins suddenly.'
  - '2. The wind groans again. At the start of the

    next morning a new Season
    begins,

    skipping next Season in line and moving

    immediately to the
    following Season.

    Birds screech and cry.'
  - '3. The next Season begins suddenly. Milk

    finches are singing out of season,
    pushing

    their milk-filled eggs from their nests,

    breaking on the ground.'
  - '4. The next Season is skipped, the following

    Season beginning suddenly.
    A grey adder,

    hisses from a nearby branch, beckoning

    the Knights over.
    It will whisper "the

    Wheel is broken" before biting anybody

    who lingers.'
  - '5. An especially intense Winter arrives

    suddenly and will not end until
    the Wheel

    is repaired. Swirling clouds form above

    the Wheel''s Hex,
    spinning at an irregular,

    stuttering pace.'
  - '6. The Wheel vanishes. Now it can only be

    found in a distant Realm (see
    opposite).'
  verse: 'Dawn, day, then dusk. Blossom, burn, then bite.

    Green, grown, then
    grey. Aborn, alive, abyss.'
  castEntries:
  - name: Guardian of the Wheel, Hewgol
    statBlock: 'VIG 18, CLA 8, SPI 8, 10 GD

      A3 (mail, gold plate, helm)'
    notes: 'Greataxe (2d10 long). Can only be lifted by a

      sworn Guardian of
      the Wheel. Can Deny.

      Cannot fathom that the Wheel isn''t working.'
  - name: Grey Adder
    statBlock: 'VIG 6, CLA 18, SPI 5, 4 GD

      Bite (d6, poisons on a Wound, the
      victim is'
    notes: unable to speak until forgiven by a snake)
  flavorTable:
    title: A DISTANT REALM
    columns:
    - header: How far away?
      values:
      - Neighbour Realm
      - Two Realms over
      - Three Realms over
      - Deep underground
      - Months over sea
      - Impossibly far
    - header: Environment
      values:
      - Desert
      - Jungle
      - Swamp
      - Mountains
      - Archipelago
      - Tundra
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
